mbpfan is a daemon that uses input from coretemp module and sets the
fan speed using the applesmc module. This version assumes any number
of processors and fans (max. 10).

- It only uses the temperatures from the processors as input.
- It requires coretemp and applesmc kernel modules to be loaded.
- It requires root use
- It daemonizes or stays in foreground
- Verbose mode for both syslog and stdout
- Users can configure it using the file /etc/mbpfan.conf

Tested Mac Models
https://github.com/linux-on-mac/mbpfan/wiki/Tested-Mac-Models
